summary.seg:
The manuscript is composed of three parts, the first two of which are
                often referred to as a single part in the scholarly tradition: 

Part Ia: Nn.3.15.1, ff. 2r-30v (15th century);

Part Ib: Nn.3.15.1, ff. 50r-114v (14th century);

Part II Nn.3.15.2, ff. 1r-152v (15th century).

collation.p:
Part Ib of the manuscript consists of 9 quaternions:
Quire 58-2 ff. 50r-55v;
Quires 6-128 ff. 57r-112v;
Quire 134-2 ff. 113r-114v.

support.material:
ff. 1r-152v Western paper, folded in quarto. Watermarks: Coat of arms ( 40 30 ) near the gutter comparable to Briquet, 2064-6, dated 1464-1478;
Bull's head ( 40 120 ) near the gutter comparable to Briquet, 14765, dated 1477;
Balance ( 90 40 ) near the gutter comparable to Briquet, 2451, dated 1475-1479;
Scissors ( 75 30 ) near the gutter comparable to Briquet, 3668, dated 1454-1462.

collation.p:
Part II of the manuscript consists of 18 quaternions, one binion and one
                      quinion: 

Quires 14-218 ff. 1r-64v;

Quire 228-3 ff. 65r-69v
                                        (the sixth, seventh and eighth leaves are cancelled, without any
                            loss of text; stubs are preserved
                            between ff. 69v and 70r);

Quire 234 ff. 70r-73v;

Quire 2410 ff. 74r-83v
                                        (the last leaf has been substituted;
                             stubs are preserved between ff.
                              73v and 74r, and 82v
                            and 83r);

Quires 25-328 ff. 84r-147v
                                        (quires 25 and 30 are folded inside out; quire 31 is misplaced);

Quire 338-2 ff. 148r-152v.
